editorialSummary.text: Easygoing spot offering classic pub grub & a full bar in a whimsical setting with Victorian details.

originalText.text:
Had B-Day reservations  made a month prior. Got there  on time@10pm had to wait for the table more then 15 minutes.  Host was a bit rude, didn't apologize for the wait or even said Happy Bday to my wife. Got the table in the back of the restaurant  ( FYI space is super tiny) and  another 10 more minutes  passed  and then the waiter came. Her name was Emma and the first  thing she said is the: "kitchen  close at11!!"
Sat down and is almost 10:35pm! We rushed and order...we were aware the menu was very simple  and we ate before but we were excited  for the drinks! Big disappointment...they were water down and super basic. Food was awful and  while we were eating some other servers  were asking if we were  done to take the plates  and honestly  I had to ask if they wanted us to leave.??...and then they said: " No we close at 1am"!! Music was extremely  loud, they had eighties  music witch we love don't take me wrong but is almost Christmas!! Maybe some classical  music would have help the atmosphere. In  general,  the place is way overrated,  decor was nice but not as beautiful  as the pictures. It is fair to say that we will Not be going back to Lillie's!

originalText.text:
Super cute decorations. The cocktails were cute/pretty/fancy but I wouldn't say my drink was particularly good. That said,  I really loved the decor and would be totally willing to give it another try.

The staff was AMAZING. We just wanted to grab a quick drink and preferred a table. They allowed us to occupy a table for 45 minutes before the reservation came in. Thank you to the staff!!!

originalText.text: Take a trip back in time at this place! Great ambience, friendly staff, and it's convenient if you going to see a show.. the food is tasty and has big portions. You can order from the regular menu or bar one even if you are a table. James Dean old fashioned is fire.

originalText.text:
We stopped in for brunch before seeing a show. We absolutely loved the holiday decor and the food!

The service was just okay, it took a long time to get anything, and after asking for the check it took close to 15 minutes for the server to return.

The table next to us ordered eggs which still hadn't come out 30 mins after receiving the rest of their order.

originalText.text:
This place is definitely one of the most Instagrammable places we've been to so far. We went around Halloween, and the decoration was awesome. Very detailed, with even animated dolls. But the environment is not all and this place deserves a detailed review.

Unfortunately, the attention was not the best. We made a reservation, and the person in the reception was not in a very good mood (not only with us, but with everybody). Besides, by the time we reached, the restaurant was only with a few tables occupied, but still we were sent to a small table very close to one occupied. The other customers and us made fun of the situation. The waitress came asking what we were going to order, but we didn't even receive the menu. I must say that the waitress was kind, but later we realized that she was the only one attending orders in the whole restaurant. In any case, we ordered two main dishes and two drinks. One main dish came so fast, but it took a while until the other dish was brought. This would be fine, but the funny part is that the drinks also take quite a while, and the water was brought only after.

The food and drinks were good, but of course with the difference of time in the arrival, I finished much before my boyfriend.

Finally, when we finished, we had to wait quite a while for having the check. And some other time to really pay. Again, I must highlight that the waitress was very kind, but in some point there was more and more people, and she got very busy taking the orders of all the tables. There were waiters and waitresses serving the food, but only she was taking orders. The restaurant is not small, so having 2 people wouldn't be a bad idea.

In conclusion, a recommended place to go in special celebrations (Halloween , Christmas), especially for taking photos.
